## 8. Pages — Detailed UI Spec

---

### PAGE 1 — Campaign List `/campaign`
**File:** `resources/ts/pages/campaign/index.vue`

```
definePage({ meta: { layout: 'default' } })
```

**Layout:**
- Breadcrumb row: `🏠 > Campaign`
- Content row: title="Campaign", right side: `[All ▼]` dropdown + `[ 🔍 Search ]` input
- Main area: **empty state** centered
  - Button: `+ Create a Campaign` (gradient bg `#8BA6FF → #3762EE`, white text, icon `tabler-plus`)
  - Clicking → opens `SelectWorkflowModal`

**SelectWorkflowModal.vue:**
- `<VDialog>` max-width=520px
- Header: "Select Workflow Mode" (text-h6) + subtitle + X button
- 2 radio option cards stacked vertically:

  **Card 1 — Advance Workflow:**
  - Left: `<VRadio>` (unselected = grey ring)
  - Center: icon (branching svg) + title + badge chip "Recommended" (green)
  - Right side illustration (branching lines image)
  - Bullet points: "Best for high-volume outreach", "Conditional logic", "Multiple paths", "More control"

  **Card 2 — Standard Workflow (default selected):**
  - Left: `<VRadio>` (selected = blue ring)
  - Center: icon (list svg) + title
  - Right side illustration (linear list image)
  - Bullet points: "Best for beginners", "Linear steps", "No conditions", "Easy Setup"

- Footer: `Close` (outlined, grey) + `Next` (gradient btn)
  - Next → push route based on selection:
    - advanced → `/campaign/advance-campaign`
    - standard → `/campaign/standard`

