## 13. Key Coding Patterns

1. **Page meta:** `definePage({ meta: { layout: 'default' } })`
2. **Get image:** `import img from '@images/figma/filename.png'`
3. **Icons:** `tabler-*` family (tabler-speakerphone, tabler-users, tabler-file-upload, tabler-brand-linkedin, tabler-logout, tabler-target, tabler-list-check)
4. **Input fields:** Use `AppTextField` wrapper (not raw `VTextField`)
5. **SCSS:** `@use "@core-scss/template/pages/campaign";` in SFC `<style lang="scss">`
6. **Colors:** `color: rgb(var(--v-theme-primary))` or `background: var(--fig-primary)`
7. **Gradient btn:** add class `btn-gradient` on `<VBtn>`

---

## 14. Important Notes

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Work in **starter-kit** ONLY (not full-version)
> - Images go in `resources/images/figma/`
> - No new npm packages unless forced
> - Routes auto-generated by file structure — no manual router edits
> - User will share more page screenshots progressively — add them as new pages

> [!NOTE]
> - Figma design frame size: 1440×1080px (desktop base)
> - Implement **light mode only** for now (dark variants exist in Figma but skip initially)
> - The left sidebar in Figma shows a **Sidebar component** — this uses the starter-kit's existing layout system

